"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77847","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p>The Government has not considered lowering tuition fee caps for students studying STEM subjects. Higher education institutions already have the flexibility to vary their fees for STEM or other courses, provided that the fees charged do not exceed the cap.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77847/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T14:05:50.5364033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77847/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77847/answer",,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-15","Students: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what consideration he has given to lowering the tuition fee cap for students studying STEM subjects.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","205814"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77848","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-07-22","<p>BIS Ministers have met with the European Competition Commissioner and have argued the case for including parts of the glass and ceramics sector as well as the cement sector in the EU Emissions Trading Scheme and Carbon Price Floor compensation, highlighting the issues of competitiveness.</p><p>The Government understands fully concerns about the impact of the these guidelines on UK companies in these sectors and will be engaging further with the Commission to seek a review of the list of eligible sectors to include other energy intensive industries in the compensation schemes in the future.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","205711 ; 205714","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77848/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T14:31:05.803382Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77848/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77848/answer",,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-15","Glass: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what recent discussions he has had with the European Commission about inclusion of the glass manufacturing industry in Annex II to the Certain State aid measures in the context of the greenhouse gas emission allowance trading scheme post-2012; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","205708"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77849","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-07-22","<p>BIS Ministers have met with the European Competition Commissioner and have argued the case for including parts of the glass and ceramics sector as well as the cement sector in the EU Emissions Trading Scheme and Carbon Price Floor compensation, highlighting the issues of competitiveness.</p><p>The Government understands fully concerns about the impact of the these guidelines on UK companies in these sectors and will be engaging further with the Commission to seek a review of the list of eligible sectors to include other energy intensive industries in the compensation schemes in the future.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","205708 ; 205714","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77849/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T14:31:05.8815077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77849/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77849/answer",,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-15","Glass: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what discussions he has had with the European Commission about the compensation scheme for the carbon price floor and inclusion of the glass manufacturing industry in Annex II to the Certain State aid measures in the context of the greenhouse gas emission allowance trading scheme post-2012; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","205711"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77850","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-07-22","<p>BIS Ministers have met with the European Competition Commissioner and have argued the case for including parts of the glass and ceramics sector as well as the cement sector in the EU Emissions Trading Scheme and Carbon Price Floor compensation, highlighting the issues of competitiveness.</p><p>The Government understands fully concerns about the impact of the these guidelines on UK companies in these sectors and will be engaging further with the Commission to seek a review of the list of eligible sectors to include other energy intensive industries in the compensation schemes in the future.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","205708 ; 205711","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77850/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T14:31:05.6940045Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77850/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77850/answer",,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-15","Glass: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the effect on the competitiveness of the British glass, manufacturing, ceramics and mineral products industries of not being eligible for the compensation scheme for the carbon price floor; and whether he has discussed this issue with the European Commission.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","205714"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77851","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-07-22","<p>As a constituent part of UK Trade and Investment, Healthcare UK has responsibility for the provision of support and assistance to new and existing healthcare exporters of goods and services across the UK and for promoting the UK and all its constituent parts to foreign investors.</p><p>The devolved administrations are responsible for devising and implementing additional programmes to meet the particular needs of companies based in Northern Ireland, Scotland and Wales and for promoting Northern Ireland, Scotland and Wales to foreign investors.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77851/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T14:17:11.9702853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77851/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77851/answer",,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-07-15","Healthcare UK","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what services Healthcare UK offers to organisations based in the devolved regions.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","205756"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77852","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-09-01","<p>Growth Deals were announced with all 39 Local Enterprise Partnerships (LEPs) on 7 July. This followed a highly competitive process in which the Government assessed LEP Strategic Economic Plans against the published assessment criteria including value for money and deliverability. The funding for these deals will be in place for all LEPs by April 2015.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77852/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-09-01T11:39:14.3333029Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77852/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77852/answer",,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-07-15","Local Growth Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, when (a) due diligence will be completed and (b) funds will be drawn down by winning bidders under the Local Growth Fund.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","206011"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77853","Cabinet Office","false","2014-09-03","<p>The Cabinet Office identified duplicate payments worth £77,164 through the 2011/12 to 2012/13 payments review. All of the duplicate payments identified were recovered.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77853/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-09-03T14:19:39.1725218Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77853/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77853/answer",,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-07-15","Billing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the value is of duplicate supplier payments identified by his Department since 2010; and what proportion of such payments have since been recovered in each of the last two financial years.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","205966"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77854","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-23","<p>Moore Stephens undertook a Spend Recovery Analysis on five years’ worth of HM Treasury data between June 2013 and March 2014. The outcome of the analysis was that there were no duplicate supplier payments identified.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77854/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-23T08:44:14.0074979Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77854/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77854/answer",,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-15","Billing","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the value is of duplicate supplier payments identified by his Department since 2010; and what proportion of such payments have since been recovered in each of the last two financial years.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","205980"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77855","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-22","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) refunds tax to individual customers for different types of taxes throughout the year. HMRC endeavours to refund tax as soon as practicable after they identify tax is to be refunded.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","205874","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77855/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T08:23:59.7965026Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77855/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77855/answer",,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-15","Taxation: Rebates","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what average length of time was taken to provide individual taxpayers with refunds of overpaid tax in (a) the most recent year for which figures are available and (b) the preceding four years.","false","Biography information for Fiona Mactaggart","Slough","Fiona Mactaggart","205873"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77856","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-22","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) refunds tax to individual customers for different types of taxes throughout the year. HMRC endeavours to refund tax as soon as practicable after they identify tax is to be refunded.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","205873","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77856/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T08:23:59.8798948Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77856/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77856/answer",,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-15","Taxation: Rebates","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many taxpayers qualified for a refund on their 2013-14 tax payments; how many of them received the refund; and what the average value is of these refunds.","false","Biography information for Fiona Mactaggart","Slough","Fiona Mactaggart","205874"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77857","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-22","<p>Budget 2014 announced that tobacco duty rates will continue to rise by 2% above RPI each year until the end of the next Parliament.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77857/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T13:07:30.2028004Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77857/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77857/answer",,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-15","Tobacco: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will lower tax duty on cigarettes.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","205907"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77858","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-22","<p>The abolition of Air Passenger Duty bands C and D cuts up to £52 per passenger off the cost of a journey originating in Northern Ireland, including connecting flights.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77858/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T13:18:45.6958588Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77858/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77858/answer",,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-15","Air Passenger Duty: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he  has made of the direct financial benefit of the abolition of air passenger duty bands C and D to airports in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","205812"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77859","HM Treasury","false","2014-08-18","<p>It is not possible to provide the requested breakdown of the total HM Revenue and Customs spent on salaries for staff employed on tackling tobacco smuggling in the way requested. The total costs for each year are as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p>Salary Cost</p><p>(millions)</p><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>Salary cost</p><p>(millions)</p><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>Salary cost</p><p>(millions)</p><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>Salary cost</p><p>(millions)</p><p>2013-14</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p>£37.044</p></td><td><p>£36.882</p></td><td><p>£35.734</p></td><td><p>£37.731</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>HM Revenue and Customs does not operate any x-ray scanners. Border Force has responsibility for the operation of x-ray scanners as part of the joint strategy to tackle tobacco smuggling.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HM Revenue and Customs total expenditure on tobacco work since 2010-11 is detailed in the table below. This includes administration and policy, as well as enforcement.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>HMRC Activity</p></td><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>2011-12</p><p> </p></td><td><p>2012-13</p><p> </p></td><td><p>2013-14</p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total expenditure on tobacco work (millions)</p></td><td><p>£65.750</p></td><td><p>£68.918</p></td><td><p>£67.641</p></td><td><p>£76.000</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>It is not possible to provide the staff information in the format requested. However, the total figures are set out below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>HMRC Activity</p></td><td><p>2010/11</p><p>Full Time Equivalent</p></td><td><p>2011/12</p><p>Full Time Equivalent</p></td><td><p>2012/13</p><p>Full Time Equivalent</p></td><td><p>2013/14</p><p>Full Time Equivalent</p></td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td><td> </td></tr><tr><td><p>Total</p></td><td><p>758</p></td><td><p>777</p></td><td><p>777</p></td><td><p>832</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>For the year 2012/13, the UK cigarette illicit market was reported at 9%, which is half the level seen a decade ago. The illicit market share for hand-rolling tobacco is 36%, lower than in 2010/11 and significantly lower than the level seen in 2008/09, when it was 50 per cent.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel","206015 ; 206016","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77859/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-08-18T09:57:52.4265364Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77859/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77859/answer",,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-15","Tobacco: Smuggling","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much HM Revenue and Customs has spent on Tackling Tobacco Smuggling strategy in each year since 2010-11; how many of his Department's staff worked on implementing that strategy in each such year; and how many such staff were engaged in (a) detection, (b) intelligence-gathering and analysis, (c) investigations and (d) the provision of legal advice.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","206017"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77860","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-22","<p>The Help to Buy scheme is helping hardworking people realise their home-owning aspirations across the UK. Over 27,000 households have bought a new home through Help to Buy so far, and 85 per cent of these have been first-time buyers. Between 2011/12 and 2013/14 11,000 first time buyers were helped through the FirstBuy scheme</p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77860/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T16:13:16.3129874Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77860/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77860/answer",,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-15","First Time Buyers","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent assessment he has made of the success of steps taken to encourage and facilitate first time buyers and young people to get onto the property ladder.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","205895"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77861","HM Treasury","false","2014-09-01","<p>HMRC continues to work towards bringing all current HMRC Fugitives facing legal proceedings before the UK Courts. They use all available systems and resources to locate and trace individuals. This includes working closely with HMRC’s Fiscal Liaison Officers based overseas, Crown Prosecution Service, National Crime Agency, Interpol and other International Partners.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC will publish an update in due course.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77861/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-09-01T16:32:03.8997744Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77861/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77861/answer",,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-15","Tax Evasion","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 10 February 2014, Official Report, column 438W, on tax evasion, what recent progress has been made by HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) in initiating proceedings against all current HMRC fugitives; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Shabana Mahmood","Birmingham, Ladywood","Shabana Mahmood","206010"
