"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77864","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-22","<p>The Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) has recently put in place new regulations for mortgages in the UK, known as the ‘Mortgage Market Review’ (MMR). The MMR is a matter for the FCA, whose day-to-day operations are independent from government control and influence.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77864/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T16:11:37.3939077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77864/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77864/answer",,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-15","Mortgages","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps he is taking to reduce the bureaucracy required to apply for a new mortgage.","false","Biography information for Andrew Bingham","High Peak","Andrew Bingham","205997"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77865","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-21","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) monitors the performance of its contractor regularly under a range of provisions. Commercial discussions between HMRC and its suppliers are confidential.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77865/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T15:55:08.8967038Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77865/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77865/answer",,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-15","Mapeley","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when HM Revenue and Customs last audited the (a) compliance and (b) performance of Mapeley STEPS Contractor Limited in respect of the Five Year Plan under 17.1 (a) of the Private Finance Initiative contract between HM Revenue and Customs and Mapeley STEPS Contractor Limited.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","205998"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77866","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-22","<p>The main purpose of child benefit and the child tax credit is to support families in the UK. Consequently, the rules for these benefits generally do not provide for them to be paid in respect of children who live abroad.</p><p> </p><p>Nevertheless, both child benefit and the child tax credit are family benefits under EC Regulation 883/2004. This regulation protects the social security rights of nationals of all member states of the European economic area, including the UK, and Switzerland when they exercise their rights of free movement under EU law.</p><p> </p><p>I refer my hon. Friend to the reply given on 14 May 2014, <em>Official report</em>, columns 676W-677W, for details about the number of claims for family benefits paid under the EC Regulations for children resident in another member state and which member states such children reside.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77866/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T13:06:00.6556687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77866/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77866/answer",,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-15","Social Security Benefits: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many adults claim child tax credit for children not residing in the UK; and for how many children such UK child benefit is claimed.","false","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris","205924"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77867","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-21","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) monitors the performance of its contractor regularly under a range of provisions. Commercial discussions between HMRC and its suppliers are confidential.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77867/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T15:35:27.7062563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77867/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77867/answer",,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-15","Mapeley","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when HM Revenue and Customs will next audit the (a) compliance and (b) performance of Mapeley STEPS Contractor Limited in respect of the Five Year Plan under 17.1 (a) of the private finance initiative contract between HM Revenue and Customs and Mapeley STEPS Contractor Limited.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","205999"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77868","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-21","<p>The Exchequer has received over £1.1bn it would not have received without the agreement. This includes Swiss yield that has been disclosed in the Liechtenstein Disclosure Facility since entering into the Agreement.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77868/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T15:57:17.181027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77868/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77868/answer",,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-15","Taxation: Switzerland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what extra revenue HM Revenue and Customs has received since entry into force of the UK-Swiss Confederation Taxation Co-operation Agreement; and what discussions the Government is having with other jurisdictions on similar agreements on tax avoidance.","false","Biography information for Daniel Kawczynski","Shrewsbury and Atcham","Daniel Kawczynski","205846"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77869","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-21","<p>Abbey House is occupied by HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) under the provisions of the STEPS Private Finance Initiative (PFI) contract, which runs until 2 April 2021. Parkside Court is occupied by HMRC under an inter department agreement with the Land Registry, who have principal responsibility for this property; the occupancy agreement expires on 5 January 2017. Matheson House is on the HMRC estate, and the lease is not due for renewal until 2 April 2021.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77869/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T15:37:09.2905475Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77869/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77869/answer",,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-15","Revenue and Customs: Telford","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when the HM Revenue and Customs leases for Abbey House and Parkside Court in Telford are up for renewal; whether Matheson House in Telford is part of the HM Revenue and Customs estate; and, if so, when its lease is due for renewal.","false","Biography information for David Wright","Telford","David Wright","205796"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77870","HM Treasury","false","2014-10-13","<p>The UKBA was closed in March 2013.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77870/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-10-13T14:55:18.4222978Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77870/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77870/answer",,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-15","Revenue and Customs","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many HM Revenue and Customs staff in each (a) grade and (b) pay band were loaned to the UK Border Agency on 10 July 2014 to cover staffing shortfalls.","false","Biography information for David Wright","Telford","David Wright","205797"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77871","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-21","<p>HM Revenue and Customs staff numbers for Consultancy and external contractors are reported in the HMRC Annual Report and Accounts 2013-14 in the Statistical Tables, Table 5: Staff Numbers (page 83).</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hmrc-annual-report-and-accounts-2013-to-2014" target="_blank">HMRC annual report and accounts: 2013 to 2014 - Publications - GOV.UK</a></p><p> </p><p>This data is not available by business area.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77871/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T15:11:43.2179467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77871/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77871/answer",,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-15","Revenue and Customs","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many external contractors and consultants were employed in each business area in HM Revenue and Customs at the latest date for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for David Wright","Telford","David Wright","205798"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77872","HM Treasury","false","2014-07-21","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) costs for external contractors are published on the Cabinet Office.gov.uk website.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC costs for Consultancy are reported in the HMRC Annual Report and Accounts 2013-14 under Other Administration Costs: Other Expenditure (page 138) and Programme Costs: Other Programme Costs (page 140) and are audited by the National Audit Office. These costs include those for the VOA, which are consolidated with the costs for the core department.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/hmrc-annual-report-and-accounts-2013-to-2014" target="_blank">HMRC annual report and accounts: 2013 to 2014 - Publications - GOV.UK</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77872/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T15:28:43.1071141Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77872/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77872/answer",,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-07-15","Revenue and Customs","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the total cost was of employing external contractors and consultants on HM Revenue and Customs-related work in 2013-14.","false","Biography information for David Wright","Telford","David Wright","205799"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77873","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p>There have been no explicit discussions abut a ‘Building for the Future’ programme.</p><p> </p><p>However as part of the recently announced Growth Deal with The Marches Local Enterprise Partnership my officials are in regular discussion with both the Partnership and Telford and Wrekin Council about the use of land assets in Telford managed by the Homes and Communities Agency and the joint stewardship arrangements.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77873/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T15:00:06.3121038Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77873/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77873/answer",,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-15","Housing: Telford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what discussions have taken place on the future of sites in Telford as part of the Building for the Future programme.","false","Biography information for David Wright","Telford","David Wright","205800"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77874","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p>Officials are currently finalising the evaluation report before submitting it to Ministers. The findings of the evaluation will then be published in due course.</p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77874/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T14:29:07.7740619Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77874/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77874/answer",,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-15","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when he plans to publish his Department's review of the New Homes Bonus.","false","Biography information for Mr Nick Raynsford","Greenwich and Woolwich","Mr Nick Raynsford","206022"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77875","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p>Under the terms of the Proposed Final Agreement for the firefighters’ pension scheme 2015 in England the actuarial reduction for a firefighter who retired earlier than the scheme’s Normal Pension Age but at the age of 57 or above would have been calculated from the Normal Pension Age. The actuarial reduction for a firefighter who retired between the ages of 55 and 57 would have been calculated from their state pension age. However, in the light of responses received to the second consultation on the firefighters’ pension scheme 2015, the Government decided to reinstate its offer, first made in June 2013, under which all actuarial reductions in the case of early retirement are calculated from the Normal Pension Age. This decision was communicated in a letter to Chief Fire Officers and Chairs of fire authorities on 9 July 2014. The letter can be found at</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/firefighters-pension-scheme-reforms" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/firefighters-pension-scheme-reforms</a> and I have placed a copy in the Library of the House.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77875/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T15:17:59.1923073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77875/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77875/answer",,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-15","Fire Services: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, for what reasons the actuarial reduction for a firefighter who retires earlier than normal pension age under the proposed new pension scheme for firefighters is calculated from the state pension age and not the scheme's normal pension age.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","205715"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77876","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p>The Government Actuary’s Department is currently undertaking a valuation of the firefighters’ pension schemes in England as at 31 March 2012, which is expected to report later this year. There have been no other valuations of the schemes since 2009.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77876/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T15:20:23.2083564Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77876/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77876/answer",,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-15","Fire Services: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether a formal valuation of the existing firefighters' pensions schemes has been carried out since the Government Actuary's Department published its formal valuation in 2009.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","205716"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77877","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p>The pension arrangements to apply to firefighters in Northern Ireland are a matter for the Northern Ireland Executive. Northern Ireland is not covered by the Public Service Pensions Act 2013 which requires a Normal Pension Age of 60 to apply to firefighters in England, Scotland and Wales.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","205752 ; 205937","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77877/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T15:19:32.2776033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77877/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77877/answer",,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-15","Fire Services: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the terms are of the firefighter pensions offer agreed by the Northern Ireland Executive.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","205751"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77879","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p>The pension arrangements to apply to firefighters in Northern Ireland are a matter for the Northern Ireland Executive. Northern Ireland is not covered by the Public Service Pensions Act 2013 which requires a Normal Pension Age of 60 to apply to firefighters in England, Scotland and Wales.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","205751 ; 205937","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77879/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T15:19:32.5276154Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77879/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77879/answer",,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-15","Fire Services: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the suitability for other negotiations of the accrual rate for pension entitlement used within the offer agreed by the Northern Ireland Executive in negotiations on firefighter pensions.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","205752"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77881","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p>The rules governing entitlement to an ill-health pension are set out in the firefighters’ pension schemes regulations. A firefighter is entitled to an ill-health pension if they are permanently incapacitated from undertaking their role. Decisions on ill-health retirement are taken by the fire and rescue authority in the first instance and the authority is bound by the opinion of an Independent Qualified Medical Practitioner. A firefighter may appeal against an authority’s decision on an issue of a medical nature to a board of medical referees.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77881/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T15:21:25.9446779Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77881/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77881/answer",,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-15","Fire Services: Retirement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether he has tasked the National Board with setting guidelines on making decisions on ill-health retirement for firefighters.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","205753"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77882","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p>As part of my Department’s transparency programme, any spend over £250.00 is available on the Department’s website. Since January 2011, all contracts over £10,000 in value are published on Contracts Finder (<a href="https://connect.gps.gsi.gov.uk/owa/,DanaInfo=livs02.ogcbs.intranet,SSL+redir.aspx?C=69a2be988b35444e93da5e8e712195a1&amp;URL=http%3a%2f%2fwww.contractsfinder.co.uk%2f" target="_blank">http://www.contractsfinder.co.uk/</a>).</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77882/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T15:55:51.8582401Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77882/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77882/answer",,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-15","Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much his Department paid to (a) G4S, (b) Serco, (c) Sodexo, (d) GEOAmey, (e) Capita, (f) Atos, (g) Mitie, (h) Working Links, (i) A4E, (j) MTC Amey, (k) GEO Group and (l) Carillion in (i) 2010-11, (ii) 2011-12, (iii) 2012-13 and (iv) 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","205850"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77883","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p>The Firefighters’ Pension Schemes are administered locally by individual fire and rescue authorities. No assessment has been made of the administrative costs of the schemes by this Department.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","205713","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77883/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T13:40:14.2767981Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77883/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77883/answer",,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-15","Fire Services: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate he has made of the annual administrative costs of the firefighters pension scheme 1992 and the new firefighters pension scheme 2006.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","205754"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77886","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p>A reformed firefighters’ pension scheme that provided for early retirement before the Normal Pension Age of 60, without an actuarial reduction, would be unlawful under the terms of the Public Service Pensions Act 2013.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77886/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T15:22:44.6614916Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77886/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77886/answer",,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-15","Fire Services: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether the Government Actuary's Department has considered what accrual rate for the proposed 2015 firefighters' pension scheme would allow retirement at 55 without an actuarial reduction.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","205755"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77888","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p>The Firefighters’ Pension Schemes are administered locally by individual fire and rescue authorities. No assessment has been made of the administrative costs of the schemes by this Department.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","205754","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77888/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T13:40:14.5654427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77888/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77888/answer",,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-15","Fire Services: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate he has made of the administration costs of the proposed 2015 firefighters' pension scheme.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","205713"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77889","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-10-27","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given to the rt.hon. Member for Newcastle upon Tyne East (Mr Nicholas Brown) on 14 July 2014, <em>Official Report</em>, Column 532W.</p><p> </p><p>My Department does not publish regional statistics.</p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77889/answer","Keighley","Keighley","Kris Hopkins","Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77889/answer/previousversion/11586","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77889/answer/previousversion/11586","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","2014-10-27T16:41:10.1822045Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77889/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77889/answer",,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-15","Local Government: Debts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the average debt level per capita is of local authorities in (a) England and (b) the North West; and what the level of debt per capita is in Warrington Borough Council.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","205952"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77890","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p>The pension arrangements to apply to firefighters in Northern Ireland are a matter for the Northern Ireland Executive. Northern Ireland is not covered by the Public Service Pensions Act 2013 which requires a Normal Pension Age of 60 to apply to firefighters in England, Scotland and Wales.</p><p> </p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","205751 ; 205752","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77890/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T15:19:32.7932296Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77890/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/77890/answer",,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-07-15","Fire Services: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether the Northern Ireland Executive's offer to firefighters on pensions is cost neutral.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","205937"
