"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78073","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p>Duplicate payments to suppliers are shown in the table below.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Value</p></td><td><p>Financial Year</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£ 3,721,960.01</p></td><td><p>2010/11</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£ 720,052.49</p></td><td><p>2011/12</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£ 1,105,217.80</p></td><td><p>2012/13</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£ 5,352,323.62</p></td><td><p>2013/14</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The proportion of duplicate payments recovered over the last 4 years is 98.74%.</p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78073/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T13:12:00.1907292Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78073/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78073/answer",,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-15","Billing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what the value is of duplicate supplier payments identified by her Department since 2010; and what proportion of such payments have since been recovered in each of the last two financial years.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","205975"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78074","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p>DFID has rigorous internal systems and processes to ensure that its aid reaches the intended beneficiaries and delivers results. A business case is mandatory for all new funding proposals, and all cases over five million pounds are approved at ministerial level. Once a programme is underway a formal review is required annually and at completion, which assesses and records whether funds have been used for their intended purposes and the results that have been delivered. Assurance that our aid money is being used for the intended purposes is gained form a number of independent providers including Internal Audit Department.</p><p>DFID has commissioned a package of reforms to further improve programme leadership, processes and capability and strengthen our oversight of spending.</p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78074/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T11:43:02.2867178Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78074/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78074/answer",,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-15","Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps she is taking to ensure that UK aid spending is used in the manner intended.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","205922"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78075","Department for International Development","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p>The UK is contributing to the achievement of the 5% target by supporting the development of payments infrastructure, with a focus on digitisation to reduce transaction costs.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We also support piloting and scaling up mobile banking through a Technology Programme for Branchless Banking which is co-funded with the Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation, the Master Card Foundation and the Consultative Group to Assist the Poor (CGAP). As of December 2013, the Programme has helped an estimated 31 million poor people globally to access financial services.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78075/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T11:56:40.6816817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78075/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78075/answer",,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-07-15","Remittances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps the Government has taken to meet the commitment made by the G20 heads of state in the final declaration of the Cannes Summit in November 2011 to reduce the average cost of transferring remittances to 5 per cent by 2014; and what assessment she made of the likelihood of the UK meeting this commitment.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Murphy","East Renfrewshire","Mr Jim Murphy","206031"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78076","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-22","<p>Sharia law has no jurisdiction in England and Wales and the Government has no intention to change this position.</p><p> </p><p>The legal profession is independent of Government and is regulated by approved regulators for which the Legal Services Board has oversight responsibility. The Law Society is the approved regulator for solicitors under the Legal Services Act 2007. On 13 March it published a practice note on Sharia succession rules to assist its members preparing wills for clients under the law of England and Wales. The Secretary of State has not had any discussions with The Law Society about its practice note. It is not for the Government to comment on the compatibility of the guidance with equalities legislation as the courts in England and Wales interpret and apply the law.</p><p> </p><p>The guidance does not, and cannot, change the law of England and Wales. The courts will continue to apply the law of England and Wales relating to the making of wills in exactly the same way as they did before the practice note was issued.</p><p> </p><p>The judiciary of England and Wales is independent of the Government and it would not be appropriate for the Ministry of Justice to issue guidance to the judiciary on how judges are to apply or interpret the law.</p><p> </p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara","205887 ; 205888","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78076/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T16:51:04.8625884Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78076/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78076/answer",,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-15","Legal Systems: Islam","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what guidance judges will receive on settling inheritance disputes which were initially settled under the Sharia succession rules guidance issued by the Law Society.","false","Biography information for Sir Charles Walker","Broxbourne","Mr Charles Walker","205889"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78077","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-21","<p>The Ministry of Justice Court Proceedings Database holds information on defendants proceeded against, found guilty and sentenced for criminal offences in England and Wales. Centrally held data does not indicate which defendants proceeded against under Section 2 of the Child Abduction Act 1984 were not taking the child out of the UK. This information may be held by the individual courts in England and Wales but as such it could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Simon Hughes",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78077/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T11:26:56.1682443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78077/answer","Biography information for Simon Hughes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78077/answer",,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-15","Abduction: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many cases of child abduction where no attempt has been made to take the child out of the UK have reached court in each of the last five years for which figures are available; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","205826"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78078","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-22","<p>Sharia law has no jurisdiction in England and Wales and the Government has no intention to change this position.</p><p> </p><p>The legal profession is independent of Government and is regulated by approved regulators for which the Legal Services Board has oversight responsibility. The Law Society is the approved regulator for solicitors under the Legal Services Act 2007. On 13 March it published a practice note on Sharia succession rules to assist its members preparing wills for clients under the law of England and Wales. The Secretary of State has not had any discussions with The Law Society about its practice note. It is not for the Government to comment on the compatibility of the guidance with equalities legislation as the courts in England and Wales interpret and apply the law.</p><p> </p><p>The guidance does not, and cannot, change the law of England and Wales. The courts will continue to apply the law of England and Wales relating to the making of wills in exactly the same way as they did before the practice note was issued.</p><p> </p><p>The judiciary of England and Wales is independent of the Government and it would not be appropriate for the Ministry of Justice to issue guidance to the judiciary on how judges are to apply or interpret the law.</p><p> </p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara","205888 ; 205889","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78078/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T16:51:04.6907043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78078/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78078/answer",,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-15","Legal Systems: Islam","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what discussions he has had with the Law Society on its inclusion of Sharia succession rules in its guidance; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Charles Walker","Broxbourne","Mr Charles Walker","205887"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78079","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-30","<p>As part of my department’s transparency programme, any spend over £25,000 is available on the Department’s website. Since January 2011, all contracts over £10,000 in value are published on Contracts Finder (<a title="http://www.contractsfinder.co.uk/" href="http://www.contractsfinder.co.uk/" target="_blank">http://www.contractsfinder.co.uk/</a>).</p><p>The private sector has an important role to play in helping deliver much needed reforms. We remain committed to promoting a diverse market including public, private and voluntary sector, as well as ensuring rigorous contract management and high standards of behaviour.</p><p>We have undertaken a major review of contract management to ensure that we have in place robust and accountable systems.</p><p> </p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78079/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-30T15:34:00.9634946Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78079/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78079/answer",,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-15","Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much his Department paid to (a) G4S, (b) Serco, (c) Sodexo, (d) GEOAmey, (e) Capita, (f) Atos, (g) Mitie, (h) Working Links, (i) A4E, (j) MTC Amey, (k) GEO Group and (l) Carillion in (i) 2010-11, (ii) 2011-12, (iii) 2012-13 and (iv) 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","205856"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78080","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-10-13","<p>In the financial years 2011/12, 2012/13 and 2013/14 no duplicate supplier payments were made; all duplicate invoices were stopped before payment and therefore no recovery action was necessary. In 2010/11 duplicate payments totalling £8,964.35 were made. This represents a small proportion, 0.039%, of the total number of duplicate payments invoiced over the four year period. It is possible that this entire amount was recovered, however, disproportionate cost would be incurred in determining this.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78080/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-10-13T13:13:12.9098555Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78080/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78080/answer",,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-15","Billing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the value is of duplicate supplier payments identified by his Department since 2010; and what proportion of such payments have since been recovered in each of the last two financial years.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","205976"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78081","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-21","<p>Details of the number of times fathers have had access to their children restricted in each of the last five years and the reasons for those restrictions are not held centrally and can only be obtained by manually checking every case file at disproportionate costs.</p>","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Simon Hughes",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78081/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T10:53:55.3191409Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78081/answer","Biography information for Simon Hughes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78081/answer",,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-15","Custody","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate he has made of the number of times fathers have had access to their children restricted in each of the last five years for which figures are available; what the reasons were for the restrictions; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","205810"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78082","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-21","<p>The payment of child maintenance and the operation of children arrangements are two separate issues which are both vitally important for separated parents. Children have a right to care and support and parents have a responsibility to provide it, regardless of whether they are separated. There is also great benefit to most children of continued contact with both parents, regardless of the financial circumstances. A dispute about child maintenance should not therefore deprive a child of meaningful contact with the other parent and vice-versa.</p><p> </p><p>The purpose of the child maintenance scheme is to make sure that parents fulfil their financial obligations to make provision for children with whom they no longer live. The Government believes that this is something parents should be able to manage for themselves through a family-based arrangement (in the vast majority of cases). The Department for Work and Pensions provides support to help them do so through the Child Maintenance Options Service (contactable on 0800-988-0988 or via www.cmoptions.org).</p><p> </p><p>The family courts deal with arrangements for children where parents have been unable to come to an agreement themselves. Here again, parents are encouraged to resolve their differences themselves. The Children and Families Act 2014 introduced, from April 2014, a legislative requirement on those who seek to issue certain family proceedings to first attend a Mediation Information and Assessment Meeting (MIAM) to find out about family mediation. The other party is also expected to engage in the process.</p>","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Simon Hughes",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78082/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T10:49:56.8522714Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78082/answer","Biography information for Simon Hughes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78082/answer",,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-15","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether courts link maintenance and contact with respect to children following the separation of the parents; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","205811"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78083","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-07-22","<p>The Department is committed to disposing of surplus property assets expeditiously. Since the start of the Spending Review (SR10) the size of the Ministry of Justice (MoJ) estate has reduced by over 600 properties to nearly 1,500 properties. The MoJ has already released land suitable for 1,253 housing units and in 2014/15 we are expected to release land suitable for a further 300 units. Therefore we will comfortably exceed our SR10 target of releasing land suitable for 1,262 housing units.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78083/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T16:40:40.9088996Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78083/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78083/answer",,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-07-15","Land","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much land his Department has released for the purpose of building new homes since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Heidi Alexander","Lewisham East","Heidi Alexander","205779"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78084","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-07-22","<p>I recently met the Chief Electoral Officer to discuss a range of issues, including steps that might be taken to ensure a faster count at elections held under the Single Transferable Vote in Northern Ireland. I have asked the Chief Electoral Officer to work closely with the Electoral Commission to explore ways to speed up the count process at PR-STV elections in Northern Ireland with a view to implementing any reforms in advance of the 2016 Assembly elections.</p><p> </p>","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78084/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T16:55:27.6659011Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78084/answer","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78084/answer",,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-07-15","Elections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what discussions  she has had with the Electoral Office on steps to ensure that the election count process for European and other elections held in Northern Ireland is faster and more efficient.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","205894"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78085","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p>My Department does not hold records of duplicate supplier payments. The system currently operating in the Northern Ireland Office registers invoice numbers and will not allow two invoices with the same reference number to be paid. To manually search through the invoices received and paid from 2010 to date would incur disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78085/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T10:57:34.1580869Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78085/answer","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78085/answer",,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-07-15","Billing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what the value is of duplicate supplier payments identified by her Department since 2010; and what proportion of such payments have since been recovered in each of the last two financial years.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","205977"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78086","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p>The Northern Ireland Assembly is now over half way through its second term since the restoration of devolution in 2007 which of itself is a significant achievement. However, there is an urgent need to make progress on dealing with divisive issues such as flags, parading and the past. The Government also believes that implementation of welfare reform by the Executive is very important.</p><p>The Government will continue to press for progress on these matters.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78086/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T10:53:39.8429229Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78086/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78086/answer",,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-07-15","Northern Ireland Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what recent assessment she has made of the level of political stability in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","205918"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78087","Cabinet Office","false","2014-07-17","<p>The Prime Minister's Office and the Deputy Prime Minister's Office are an integral part of the Cabinet Office.</p><p>As part of my department's transparency programme, any spend over £25,000 is available on the Department's website. Since January 2011, all contracts over £10,000 in value are published on Contracts Finder (<a href="http://www.contractsfinder.co.uk/" target="_blank">http://www.contractsfinder.co.uk/</a>).</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","205853","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78087/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-17T15:43:06.4827583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78087/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78087/answer",,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-07-15","Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how much No. 10 Downing Street paid to (a) G4S, (b) Serco, (c) Sodexo, (d) GEOAmey, (e) Capita, (f) Atos, (g) Mitie, (h) Working Links, (i) A4E, (j) MTC Amey, (k) GEO Group and (l) Carillion in (i) 2010-11, (ii) 2011-12, (iii) 2012-13 and (iv) 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","205857"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78088","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-07-22","<p>It is a commercial matter for Farnborough International Ltd (FIL) to whom they sell exhibition space, however the Prime Minister has not received any representations following their decision to allow Rosoboronexport to exhibit. In light of the continuing suspension of military cooperation with Russia, no representatives from the Russian government were issued with Her Majesty’s Government (HMG) invitations to the event. Russia was also removed from the list of countries eligible to use post-exhibition Open General Export Licenses (OGELs). The organisers also took the decision to ensure that no Russian military hardware was displayed and that there was no Russian military participation in the flying display.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78088/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T14:17:36.9803656Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78088/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78088/answer",,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-07-15","Air Displays: Farnborough","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he received on the decision to give permission to the Russian company Rosoboronexport to exhibit its military technology at the Farnborough International Air show in July 2014.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","205928"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78089","Department of Health","false","2014-07-22","<p>51% of the women classified as “single” in Abortion Statistics 2013 were in a relationship but not married or in a civil partnership.</p><p> </p><p>More broadly, the Government’s <em>Framework for Sexual Health Improvement in England </em>(March 2013) highlights the importance of building knowledge and resilience amongst young people so they have the confidence and emotional resilience to understand the benefits of loving, healthy relationships and delaying sex.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78089/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T16:05:35.9697696Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78089/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78089/answer",,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-15","Abortion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, With reference to the findings of his Department's Abortion Statistics 2013, published in June 2014, paragraph 2.4, that 81 per cent of abortions in that year were carried out for single women, if he will take steps to reduce the abortion rate by encouraging couples to stay together.","false","Biography information for Mr Joe Benton","Bootle","Mr Joe Benton","205993"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78090","Public Accounts Commission","false","2014-07-21","<p>The following table sets out the number of National Audit Office (NAO) staff who have remained at that grade since 2010 and received a pay rise.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Grade</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Number</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Band 1</p><p>Band 2</p><p>Band 3</p><p>Admin Officer (Audit)</p><p>Executive Officer (Audit)</p><p>Audit Technician</p><p>Analyst</p><p>Senior Analyst</p><p>Audit Principal</p><p>Audit Manager</p><p>Director</p><p>Director General</p><p>Executive Leader</p><p>Chief Operating Officer</p></td><td><p>7</p><p>29</p><p>33</p><p>1</p><p>1</p><p>3</p><p>6</p><p>21</p><p>116</p><p>86</p><p>28</p><p>1</p><p>2</p><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>335</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78090/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T08:33:07.3374604Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78090/answer","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78090/answer",,,"24","Public Accounts Commission","Public Accounts Commission","2014-07-15","Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chairman of the Public Accounts Commission, how many employees of the National Audit Office, broken down by grade, have remained at the same grade since 2010 and in that period received pay rises.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","205745"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78091","Scotland Office","false","2014-07-21","<p>As part of my department’s transparency programme, any spend over £25,000 is available on the Department’s website. Since January 2011, all contracts over £10,000 in value are published on Contracts Finder (<a href="http://www.contractsfinder.co.uk/" target="_blank">http://www.contractsfinder.co.uk/</a>).</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78091/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T13:17:53.2960549Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78091/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78091/answer",,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-07-15","Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how much his Department paid to (a) G4S, (b) Serco, (c) Sodexo, (d) GEOAmey, (e) Capita, (f) Atos, (g) Mitie, (h) Working Links, (i) A4E, (j) MTC Amey, (k) GEO Group and (l) Carillion in (i) 2010-11, (ii) 2011-12, (iii) 2012-13 and (iv) 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","205858"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78092","Scotland Office","false","2014-07-21","<p>The Scotland Office has made no duplicate supplier payments since 2010.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78092/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T13:16:27.2504136Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78092/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78092/answer",,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-07-15","Billing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what the value is of duplicate supplier payments identified by his Department since 2010; and what proportion of such payments have since been recovered in each of the last two financial years.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","205978"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78093","Speaker's Committee for the Independent Parliamentary Standards Authority","false","2014-09-12","<p> </p><p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the Independent Parliamentary Standards Authority. I have asked IPSA to reply.</p><p> </p><p><em>Letter from Marcial Boo, July 2014:</em></p><p> </p><p>As Chief Executive of the Independent Parliamentary Standards Authority, I have been asked to reply to your Parliamentary Question asking about IPSA staffing.</p><p> </p><p>29 of our current employees have worked for IPSA since 2010. Of those 29, 17 have remained at the same grade and received pay rises of 1% in 2012 and 2013.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Grade</p></td><td><p>Number</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>A</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>B</p></td><td><p>11</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>C</p></td><td><p>3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>D</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>E</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>F</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Broxbourne","Mr Charles Walker",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78093/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-09-12T13:32:41.3994046Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78093/answer","Biography information for Sir Charles Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78093/answer",,,"90","Speaker's Committee for the Independent Parliamentary Standards Authority","Speaker's Committee for the Independent Parliamentary Standards Authority","2014-07-15","Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for Broxbourne, representing the Speaker's Committee for the Independent Parliamentary Standards Authority, how many employees of the Independent Parliamentary Standards Authority, broken down by grade, have remained at the same grade since 2010 and in that period received pay rises.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","205746"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78094","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","false","2014-07-24","<p> </p><p>The Commission’s staff are not members of the civil service. It does not apply a civil service grading structure with incremental scales and so cannot provide the information as requested.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In 2010-11 and 2011-12 there were no pay awards given to its staff. In subsequent years the 1% public sector pay cap has been applied to all of its staff.</p><p> </p>","South West Devon","Mr Gary Streeter",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78094/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-24T13:36:59.6664327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78094/answer","Biography information for Sir Gary Streeter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78094/answer",,,"36","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","2014-07-15","Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for South West Devon, representing the Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission, how many employees of the Commission, of each grade, have remained at the same grade since 2010 and in that period received pay rises.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","205747"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78096","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p>In 2011, £28,861 of duplicate supplier payments were identified by the Department and its agencies, and were all recovered. No duplicate payments have been identified in subsequent years.</p><p> </p><p>In accordance with Cabinet Office guidelines, the Department commissioned a spend recovery audit in 2010. This reported that:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p><em>The quantity of payment errors identified during our review (0.0002%) highlighted that the internal controls used by DfT have been effective in limiting supplier overpayments. Overall the accounts payable function is well managed and controlled.</em></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In view of this advice, the DfT decided that formal appraisal of potential duplicate payments, either internal or external, did not represent a good use of public money for the years after 2011.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78096/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T14:06:51.7351303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78096/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78096/answer",,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-15","Billing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the value is of duplicate supplier payments identified by his Department since 2010; and what proportion of such payments have since been recovered in each of the last two financial years.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","205979"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78097","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p>As part of the department’s transparency programme, any spend over £25,000 is available on the Department’s website. Since January 2011, all contracts over £10,000 in value are published on Contracts Finder (<a href="http://www.contractsfinder.co.uk/" target="_blank">http://www.contractsfinder.co.uk/</a>).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78097/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T14:00:49.9413061Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78097/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78097/answer",,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-15","Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much his Department paid to (a) G4S, (b) Serco, (c) Sodexo, (d) GEOAmey, (e) Capita, (f) Atos, (g) Mitie, (h) Working Links, (i) A4E, (j) MTC Amey, (k) GEO Group and (l) Carillion in (i) 2010-11, (ii) 2011-12, (iii) 2012-13 and (iv) 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","205859"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78098","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p>As stated in the Greater Lincolnshire Deal, which was part of the Local Growth Fund announcement on 7 July, the Department is committed to working with D2N2 and the Greater Lincolnshire Local Enterprise Partnership and partners to help achieve their objective of increased service frequency between Lincoln and Nottingham via Newark.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>However, this is dependent on the affordability and value for money of the services. In addition, it is dependent on the level of local funding available to support these incremental rail services for the first three years, after which the Department would consider continuing with the services as part of its base specification. We are currently assessing the available options against the criteria above, taking account of likely revenue and cost implications alongside the latest funding offer from the stakeholders.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78098/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T15:29:46.9759538Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78098/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78098/answer",,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-15","Railways: East Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of options for increasing service frequencies on the Nottingham-Lincoln line; and what the revenue subsidy and capital cost of implications are of each such option.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","205825"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78099","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p>The Economic Case for HS2 published in October 2013 (which can be found at: <a href="http://assets.hs2.org.uk/sites/default/files/inserts/S%26A%201_Economic%20case_0.pdf" target="_blank">http://assets.hs2.org.uk/sites/default/files/inserts/S%26A%201_Economic%20case_0.pdf</a>), estimates that in 2036 and thereafter, 3.6% of the revenue generated by Phase 1 of HS2 originates from commuters travelling between the West Midlands and London.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78099/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T16:02:02.1660222Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78099/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78099/answer",,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-15","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much of the estimated income included in the business case for phase 1 of High Speed 2 comes from Birmingham to London commuters.","false","Biography information for Frank Dobson","Holborn and St Pancras","Frank Dobson","205819"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78100","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p>The Secretary of State for Transport met with Edwina Hart the Minister for Economy, Science and Transport, National Assembly for Wales on 16<sup>th</sup> July 2014, to discuss the rail connectivity in North Wales which included Halton Curve.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78100/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T14:23:38.9772234Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78100/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78100/answer",,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-15","Railways: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent discussions he has had with the (a) Welsh Government and (b) Secretary of State for Wales on improving rail connectivity with north Wales utilising the Halton Curve.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian Lucas","205933"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78101","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p>This scheme involves the installation of new crossovers at Halton and Frodsham with a track upgrade enabling trains to operate in both directions. This work reinstates a rail link which will enable passenger services from North Wales and West Cheshire to directly access Liverpool City Centre and Liverpool John Lennon airport. Further details of the work to be provided by Network Rail early next year.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78101/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T14:16:24.6806161Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78101/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78101/answer",,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-15","Railways: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what works will be undertaken as part of the upgrade of the Halton Curve.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian Lucas","205931"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78102","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p>The exact service patterns have not yet been determined by Network Rail and stakeholders. Further announcements expected 2016/17.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78102/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T14:11:35.0588335Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78102/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78102/answer",,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-15","Railways: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on rail journeys in (a) Wales and (b) the North West of the upgrade of the Halton Curve.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian Lucas","205930"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78103","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p>The Government is providing £10.4m, in support of the Liverpool City Region Growth Deal, to fund the reinstatement of the Halton Curve. The scheme is currently being developed by Network Rail and detailed proposals are expected to be available early next year. Final sign off of funding for the scheme will be for the Liverpool City Region Local Enterprise Partnership and delivery is expected in 2016/17.</p><p> </p><p /> <p /><p />","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78103/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T14:20:34.503109Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78103/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78103/answer",,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-15","Railways: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what timescale the upgrade of the Halton Curve will follow.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian Lucas","205932"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78104","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p>The Blue Badge Scheme Local Authority Guidance (England) is not mandatory as it is non-statutory guidance. It is guidance for local authorities on best practice in administering the Blue Badge Scheme.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78104/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T16:07:39.4879548Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78104/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78104/answer",,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-15","Blue Badge Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether guidance issued to local authorities on the Blue Badge scheme is mandatory; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","205809"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78105","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><em><strong><em>The Regional Air Connectivity Fund has not currently been used to support air links to and from Northern Ireland. </em></strong></em><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><em><strong><em>The fund can be used maintain existing domestic air connectivity to London where there is a risk that an existing link may be lost, and to provide financial support to develop new routes from airports of less than five million passengers per year.</em></strong></em><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><em><strong><em>Northern Ireland is well-connected by air to London with over 18,000 flights per year between the two Belfast airports and the five main London airports, carrying over two million passengers. The first use of this fund was announced earlier this summer to protect the air route between Dundee and London through a Public Service Obligation. </em></strong></em><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><em><strong><em>With regards to providing Start-up aid for new routes, the Department for Transport is working with the Treasury to develop guidance that will clarify how the Government will expect to interpret the European Union State aid guidelines on start-up aid for new air routes. The Department for Transport expects to publish this guidance in the autumn.</em></strong></em><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78105/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T16:13:47.4903587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78105/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78105/answer",,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-15","Aviation: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the Regional Air Connectivity Fund has been used to support air links to and from Northern Ireland since that fund was created.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","205794"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78106","Department for Transport","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p>Investment in HS2 will deliver widespread connectivity improvements, grow markets and increase opportunities to trade.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Economic Case for HS2 published in October 2013 estimates that 17% of the transport user benefits of the HS2 Y-Network are generated from trips originating in the North West. This equates to benefits of approximately £342m (PV, 2011 prices) in 2036. Further analysis by KPMG suggests the wider economic effects could be far greater.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78106/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T16:09:36.2342889Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78106/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78106/answer",,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-07-15","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the net economic effect of High Speed 2 for the North-West.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","206042"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78107","Wales Office","false","2014-07-21","<p> </p><p>As part of my Department’s transparency programme, any spend over £500 is available on the Department’s website. Since January 2011, all contracts over £10,000 in value are published on Contracts Finder: <a title="blocked::http://www.contractsfinder.co.uk/" href="http://www.contractsfinder.co.uk/" target="_blank">http://www.contractsfinder.co.uk/</a>.</p><p> </p>","Preseli Pembrokeshire","Stephen Crabb",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78107/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T09:14:21.4268958Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78107/answer","Biography information for Stephen Crabb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78107/answer",,,"28","Wales","Wales","2014-07-15","Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how much his Department paid to (a) G4S, (b) Serco, (c) Sodexo, (d) GEOAmey, (e) Capita, (f) Atos, (g) Mitie, (h) Working Links, (i) A4E, (j) MTC Amey, (k) GEO Group and (l) Carillion in (i) 2010-11, (ii) 2011-12, (iii) 2012-13 and (iv) 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","205860"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78108","Wales Office","false","2014-07-22","<p> </p><p>The Wales Office has identified no duplicate payments since 2010.</p><p> </p>","Preseli Pembrokeshire","Stephen Crabb",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78108/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T10:40:16.5311815Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78108/answer","Biography information for Stephen Crabb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78108/answer",,,"28","Wales","Wales","2014-07-15","Billing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what the value is of duplicate supplier payments identified by his Department since 2010; and what proportion of such payments have since been recovered in each of the last two financial years.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Mr Tom Watson","205981"
