"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78134","Cabinet Office","false","2014-07-17","<p>A list of official Twitter accounts run by Cabinet Office, including those used by senior officials, can be found at <a href="https://twitter.com/cabinetofficeuk/cabinet-office-teams/members" target="_blank">https://twitter.com/cabinetofficeuk/cabinet-office-teams/members</a>. The department also runs the @Number10gov and @Number10press accounts.</p><p>No member of staff is employed to specifically work on social media.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78134/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-17T15:10:04.1008617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78134/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78134/answer",,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-07-15","Social Media","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many Twitter accounts are run by his Department; how much his Department spends annually on (a) Twitter accounts and (b) all social media; and how many people in his Department are employed to work on social media.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206049"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78135","Department of Health","false","2014-07-22","<p>On 19 March 2014, the Supreme Court handed down a judgment that clarified the test for what constitutes a deprivation of liberty. The clarified test is: “An individual who lacks the mental capacity to consent to the arrangements for his or her care and is under continuous control and supervision and is not free to leave”.</p><p> </p><p>Following the judgment, the Department issued an advice note to health and care professionals and local authorities to highlight this legal interpretation and its implications.</p><p> </p><p>The Department is currently monitoring the effects of the judgment on the health and care system and on local authorities. The Health and Social Care Information Centre will carry out an additional voluntary data collection. This will gather information from local authorities on how many applications have been received for authorisations in care homes and hospitals under the Deprivation of Liberty Safeguards since the judgment. We expect the data to be available in October 2014; this will facilitate an assessment of the judgment’s impact.</p><p> </p><p>At the Department’s request, the Association of Directors of Adult Social Services is leading a task group to consider the implications of the judgment. This group has representation from local authorities, NHS England, the Care Quality Commission and the Department. The group intends to issue advice in the autumn.</p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78135/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T13:33:12.0770432Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78135/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78135/answer",,,"17","Health","Health","2014-07-15","Patients' Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the effect of the recent Supreme Court ruling concerning which individuals in care homes and hospitals should be subject to a deprivation of liberty assessment; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Maria Miller","Basingstoke","Maria Miller","206097"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78136","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-07-21","<p>No specific discussions have taken place with the National Lottery about the use of Lottery funding in relation to the video games industry. This Government has restored the Lottery shares for heritage sports, and arts good causes to 20%, so contributing to a significant increase in Lottery funding for those areas since the beginning of this Parliament. It is for individual Distributing bodies to determine the beneficiaries of Lottery monies in making awards within their good cause sectors, taking account of their Policy Directions.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78136/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T09:53:28.965757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78136/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78136/answer",,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-15","National Lottery: Video Games","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what discussions he has had with the National Lottery about extending funding to the video games industry.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","205946"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78137","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-07-22","<p>The Government is investing £780 million, with local match funding, to provide superfast broadband coverage to 95% of UK premises, including in rural locations. Coverage will include both business and residential consumers. In addition, the Government has also launched 8 pilot projects to explore options for improving coverage of superfast broadband beyond 95%, including to the most hard to reach areas of the UK.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78137/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-22T09:00:41.8571044Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78137/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78137/answer",,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-07-15","Broadband: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps his Department is taking to improve the broadband infrastructure for businesses in rural areas.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","205773"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78138","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-21","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave him on 8 November 2013, (Official Report, column 399W). The Major Project Report 2013 reported the cost of the Queen Elizabeth class carriers at £6.102 billion (£6.2 Billion less assessment phase costs that do not fall under the remit of the Major Projects Report).</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78138/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T15:50:49.8362831Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78138/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78138/answer","20131108 Hansard extract Aircraft Carriers[1].doc","20131108 Hansard extract","11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Aircraft Carrier Alliance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will estimate how much contract overruns in the Aircraft Carrier Alliance have cost the public purse to date.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","206045"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78139","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-21","<p>Military Aviation Authority (MAA) Regulatory Instruction 02/11, issued on 28 January 2011, mandated a Risk Management framework to support Aviation Duty Holder decision making and replace existing procedures. This was superseded by Regulatory Article 1210 on 1 August 2011.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78139/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T15:53:53.4996198Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78139/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78139/answer",,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Military Aircraft: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when Military Aviation Authority Regulatory Article 1210 replaced Ministry of Defence Business Procedure 1201 with regards to air safety.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","206047"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78140","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-07-21","<p>The Royal Navy Merlin Mk1 fleet is being modernised through the Merlin Capability Sustainment Programme. A total of 30 Merlin Mk1 helicopters are being modified to address existing and forecast avionic obsolescence and will then be known as the Merlin Mk2. The approved cost of the Demonstration and Manufacture phases of the programme is £805 million.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78140/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-07-21T15:54:41.8725291Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78140/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78140/answer",,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Merlin Helicopters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many additional Merlin helicopters will be upgraded from Mk1 standard to Mk2; and what the total cost of each upgrade will be.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","206046"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78141","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-02","<p> </p><p>It is not possible to provide the total value of payouts under the War Pensions Scheme to forces personnel and veterans on the grounds of mental ill health as the information is not held in a format that would enable us to easily answer the question and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.<br><br>However, between 2011-12 and 2013-14 there were a total of 1,655 awards made under the War Pension Scheme for a mental health condition related to Service.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78141/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-09-02T14:24:50.5906581Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78141/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78141/answer",,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Armed Forces: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the value of pay outs under the War Pensions Scheme to forces personnel and veterans on the grounds of mental ill health has been in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206073"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78142","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-02","<p> </p><p>It is not possible to provide the value of payouts made to Armed Forces veterans and their families under the Armed Forces Pension Scheme as a result of service in Afghanistan as the information is not held in a format that would enable us to easily answer the question and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.<br><br>The AFPS is primarily an occupational pension scheme, the Pensions Computer system does not identify the conflicts in which Service Personnel have served.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78142/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-09-02T14:28:24.7375762Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78142/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78142/answer",,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Afghanistan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the total value of payouts to armed forces veterans and their families under the Armed Forces Pension Scheme as a result of service in Afghanistan has been in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206076"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78143","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-04","<p>The average length of time taken to process claims under the War Pensions Scheme in each year since 2010 has been;<br><br>2010-11 – 39 working days<br>2011-12 – 51 working days<br>2012-13 – 82 working days<br>2013-14 – 110 working days<br>2014-15 year to 31 July – 102 working days<br><br>In the majority of cases deadlines for progressing cases are met. The War Pensions and Armed Forces Compensation Schemes are jointly resourced and administered. The impact of the implementation of the Boyce Review on the Armed Forces Compensation Scheme (Cm 7798, published February 2010) and its subsequent publicity campaign, combined with an increase in the number of applications for War Disablement Pension (linked to more people with pre-April 2005 service reaching the end of their engagement), led to delays in processing prospective claims.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78143/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-09-04T12:50:05.7954011Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78143/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78143/answer",,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","War Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the average length of time taken to process settlements for the War Pensions Scheme has been in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206082"
