"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78148","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-08-07","<p> </p><p> </p><p>The amounts paid in the UK and abroad in regard to the two categories in question, including legal costs, were as follows:</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p><p>Structural/Property damage</p></td><td>Amount paid</td><td>Highest payment</td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>£185,000</p></td><td><p>£125,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>£42,000</p></td><td><p>£6,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>£122,000</p></td><td><p>£7,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>£202,000</p></td><td><p>£15,000</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td>Loss of Livestock</td><td><p> </p><p>Amount paid</p></td><td>Highest payment</td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>£114,000</p></td><td><p>£23,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>£443,000</p></td><td><p>£23,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>£290,000</p></td><td><p>£15,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>£521,000</p></td><td><p>£15,000</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>These amounts do not include payments made by the Area Claims Office in Afghanistan, which are not recorded in a manner that can distinguish without incurring disproportionate cost between those claims relating to structural damage to private property and those relating to loss of livestock. The overall payments for damage to property, including legal costs, made over the periods in question in Afghanistan were as follows:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p>Amount paid</p></td><td><p>Highest payment</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>£1,200,000</p></td><td><p>£143,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>£436,000</p></td><td><p>£15,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>£677,000</p></td><td><p>£9,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>£230,000</p></td><td><p>£20,000</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78148/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-08-07T10:45:06.2543664Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78148/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78148/answer",,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the value is of compensation payouts issued by his Department on the grounds of (a) structural damage to private property and (b) loss of livestock in each year since 2010; and what the highest such payment in each case has been.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206066"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78149","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-01","<p>The total number of claims submitted under the War Pensions Scheme in each year since 2010 are;</p><p><br>2010-11 – 24,345<br>2011-12 – 22,520<br>2012-13 – 21,865<br>2013-14 – 21,460</p><p>In line with Defence statistics rounding policy all figures have been rounded to the nearest 5.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78149/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-09-01T16:49:34.7910088Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78149/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78149/answer",,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","War Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many claims have been submitted to the War Pensions Scheme in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206081"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78150","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-09-01","<p>There were no claims brought forward under the Armed Forces Pension Scheme in each year since 2010. The number of outstanding claims under the War Pensions Scheme in each year since 2010 is;</p><p>2010-11 – 3,695<br>2011-12 – 5,775<br>2012-13 – 9,210<br>2013-14 – 7,645</p><p>In line with Defence statistics rounding policy all figures have been rounded to the nearest 5.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78150/answer",,,,,,,,,"2014-09-01T16:46:05.5223436Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78150/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/78150/answer",,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-07-15","Armed Forces: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many claims have been brought forward under the (a) Armed Forces Pension Scheme and (b) War Pensions Scheme in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","206074"
